    <h1>Ok&#xAD;to&#xAD;ber&#xAD;fest With Brotzeit</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200911/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-11"><time>2020-09-11</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Ger­man restau­rant Brotzeit’s menu is cu­rated by its new group ex­ec­u­tive chef Lorenz Raich, who has worked in Miche­lin-starred kitchens and bou­tique venues. High­lights in­clude Cold Roast Pork ($16++), made with slices of slow-roasted pork col­lar and served with house-pick­led daikon, rocket leaves and mus­tard aioli; Crispy Fried Pig Ears ($12++); and a Gi­ant Pret­zel with Farmer’s Sausage ($28++). This year, Brotzeit will be the only restau­rant in Singapore serv­ing Ok­to­ber­fest­bier from Hof­brau, a Mu­nich brew­ery with more than 400 years of his­tory. The full-bod­ied, hoppy beer has a slightly sweet fin­ish which pairs well with rich foods such as roast meats and hard cheeses.</p>
    <p>WHERE (MRT): 01-149/151 VivoCity, 1 Har­bourFront Walk (Har­bourFront); 01-17 Raf­fles City Shop­ping Cen­tre, 252 North Bridge Road (City Hall);</p>
    <p>126 East Coast Road (Eunos);</p>
    <p>01-04 West­gate, 3 Gate­way Drive (Jurong East) WHEN: Tue - Oct 25, 11am - 10.30pm daily</p>
    <p>brotzeit.co/pro­mo­tion/brunch</p>


